### State-level Consecutive Day Trends {.tabset .tabset-pills}

> Of the 51 US states monitored, **`r state_metrics_cat_consec %>% filter(trend == "rising", days >= 7) %>% nrow()` (`r round(state_metrics_cat_consec %>% filter(trend == "rising", days >= 7) %>% nrow()/51 * 100, 2)`%) ** show consecutive increase in their 7-day moving average of new COVID-19 cases for at least 7 days. **`r state_metrics_cat_consec %>% filter(trend == "decreasing", days >= 7) %>% nrow()` (`r round(state_metrics_cat_consec %>% filter(trend == "decreasing", days >= 7) %>% nrow()/51 * 100, 2)`%)** show consecutive decrease for at least 7 days.
 
#### **`r state_metrics_cat_consec %>% filter(trend == "rising", days >= 7) %>% nrow()`** State(s) with Consecutive Increase
<center>
```{r echo=FALSE, warning=FALSE, results='asis'}
# top ten states with 14 days continuous case increase based on cases/capita 100,000
# table function

table_consec_fun("rising")
```
</center>


####  **`r state_metrics_cat_consec %>% filter(trend == "decreasing", days >= 7) %>% nrow()`** State(s) with Consecutive Decrease

<center>
```{r echo=FALSE, warning=FALSE, results='asis'}
# top ten states with 14 days continuous case increase based on cases/capita 100,000

table_consec_fun("decreasing")

```








### Hospital Status
 

> The following illustrates the current situation in hospitals in the USA. On average, the stress on intensive care units (ICUs) across the country is *`r icu_phrase`* and the usage of inpatient centers by covid-19 patients is *`r inpatient_phrase`*.



<center>
```{r echo=FALSE, warning=FALSE, message=FALSE}

icu_stress %>% 
  mutate(label = if_else(collection_date == max(collection_date), as.character(paste0(round(avg, 2), "%")), NA_character_)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = collection_date, 
            y = avg)) +
  geom_line(
            color = "dark green",
            size = 2) + 
  scale_colour_discrete(guide = 'none')  + 
  geom_label_repel(aes(label = label),
                  nudge_x = 5,
                  na.rm = TRUE) +
    ggtitle(paste0("%Est. Staffed Adult ICU \nBeds Occupied in USA \n(", min(icu$collection_date), " to ", max(icu$collection_date),")")) +
  xlab("") +
  ylab("% Staffed Adult ICU Beds Occupied") +
  theme_economist()

```
</center>


